  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Analysis, reflection and information advocating for democracy and human rights in Central America</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This initiative is aimed to contribute to social change in Central America producing and disseminating critical research on the regional reality.  After four decades sharing reliable and opportune information periodically through Env&#xED;o Magazine (digital and printed versions), partner continues developing a high quality analysis focused on the main issues related to human rights, political context and citizenship with a holistic approach, promoting a deep understanding of their structural causes and trends.  Key regional stakeholders, religious and social leaders, especially in Nicaragua (where the partner is based) consider Env&#xED;o Magazine as a relevant journalistic reference. 

For the current cycle, the different activities and publications will prioritise a reflection on the risks of a new social polarisation in Honduras, Guatemala, El Salvador and Nicaragua, caused by political transitions beyond electoral processes but also because conflicts and governance crisis in each country.  Also, there is an ethical guidance in order to promote respect for cultural diversity and gender equality as cross-cutting topics. This perspective will be included in the main monthly articles and the workshops. 

Finally, the project will support the institutional efforts to improve the capabilities to manage social media and digital platforms which will allow a better monitoring of achievements in terms of reaching wider audiences.</narrative>
  </description>
